I used to go here three or four times per week last winter. It is moderately busy and as good as any Starbucks. I do not believe that they have restroom facilities available. You might need to go to the train station across the street.
Starbucks in general spends a lot of time/training on customer service but you can always tell if people are following a script originally nice. They are always friendly and helpful.

It's a decent Starbucks.  My biggest issue is their online ordering is a mess.  There's no dedicated pickup so people congregate (and a lot in the morning) around the general pickup area.  Lots of times they won't call names and it's hard to get to the front because people block the way.  Also recently I placed an online order to pickup and walked there only to find out it was out of stock.  Some workers are not the most friendly and can't even thank you for a purchase.  And then there are some other workers like Ashley that are super nice, have been there a long time, and remember your name.  So my three stars are based on the poor on-line pickup, the fact you order something online and it's not available when you go to pick it up, and that some of the newer employees aren't the most friendly.  The pics I took are from 6:15am when it's not as crowded.  8 is when it starts getting crazy.
No bathroom

I wanted to give this place a lower rating but that wouldn't be fair. I'll start by saying it has a nice amount of space and a pleasant feel. The staff is nicer than many of the abundantly indifferent Loop clerks one encounters elsewhere. They have a lot of precisely persnickety customers who slow down the line and they seem to do what they can as fast as they can, under the circumstances. The reason I withheld the 5th star has nothing to do with the staff here and everything to do with the awful changes that the company made to the rewards app. I ordered a pair of drinks "as-is" with nothing special being done to them. I used the app, as I always do, and it screwed up royally, which transformed a simple order into a production that needed management level attention. It was during this visit that I found out that any cold drink, no matter how basic; like ice tea, is now considered a "hand crafted beverage" by the app and it deducts the same amount of stars as a complicated whipped cream drink. That's just not right.

Asked for a large and she gave me a grande/medium. C'mon now. A large is a large.... I shouldn't have to use Starbucks lingo to get the right sized drink. The wait is pretty long for the number of people waiting, but at least my drink tasted great.

This Starbucks is located on the ground floor of an office building, so lines will be long during office rush times (before 8 am, 10:30 am, lunchtime). It's a busy store, so the food in particular took longer than I'm used to seeing at a Starbucks. Quality was high though, and staff were friendly.

After several visits I feel confident leaving this review. I stop by maybe once or twice a week to this Starbucks on my way to work. Every time I've been  here my drink has taken 15min+ Most of the time I order an iced coffee. It's just Coffe + Ice+ Cup. It really shouldn't take 15 mins to get that put together.  The problem here is two reasons. 1) They prioritize mobile orders over in person orders. So as people stack up and stack up in the store waiting for their coffee there will be many many mobile orders being completed. Doesn't seem logical considering you get advanced warning for the online and can plan ahead. 2) The line process seems to have issues. You order at the counter and then somewhere in between there and the pick up spot your order can just disappear. Seems like they should have solved this by now?  hopefully this place improves because the location is super convenient!
